				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">No, nothing simple. Cheapest option is definitely going to be to use a microcontroller with USB host.<br /><br />The slowest USB speed requires being able to alternate the pins at 1.5MHz.<br /><br /><em>But</em> there's a nontrivial chance that most USB keyboards still can use the PS/2 protocol, which is enough slower that it could be bit-banged by the NES.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

